# All substantive source — encrypted via git-crypt.
#
# POLICY (enforced by blanket globs, last match wins):
#   Every *.py and *.tcss file is encrypted AUTOMATICALLY — new modules,
#   screens, widgets, and tests need no entry here. Do not list source files
#   individually; that pattern silently drifted (30+ files fell out of the
#   filter between 2026-06 and 2026-07). Only add lines below to make
#   something PUBLIC, never to make something encrypted.
#   Plaintext scaffolding: README, LICENSE, requirements.txt, pyproject.toml,
#   .gitignore, assets/, data/demo/**, the `tape` launcher.

# ── Blanket rules: all source encrypted ──
*.py filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt
*.tcss filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt

# ── Docs that reveal features/architecture/thesis ──
USER_GUIDE.md filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt
ROADMAP.md filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt
docs/superpowers/** filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt

# ── Public scaffolding exceptions (plaintext) ──
data/demo/** !filter !diff
